# .cursorrules — DePress Project

## Context Protocol
- Read `architecture.md` and `process.md` BEFORE any task. They are the source of truth.
- Only work on the current Phase in `process.md`. Refuse scope creep; note out-of-phase ideas in the "Backlog" section instead of implementing.
- After completing a TODO item, update `process.md` (check the box, bump Last Updated). Do this in the same session.

## Output Discipline (token economy)
- No apologies, no preamble, no summaries of what you just did unless asked.
- For multi-file changes: output a numbered plan (≤10 lines) first, wait for approval only if the change touches >3 files or any file in `packages/ast`.
- When editing a file, output only the diff/changed sections, never re-print unchanged code.
- Never re-explain the architecture; reference `architecture.md` section numbers instead.

## Code Standards
- TypeScript strict mode; `noUncheckedIndexedAccess: true`. Never use `any`; use `unknown` + narrowing.
- All cross-boundary data (editor↔API↔worker) MUST be validated with Zod schemas from `packages/ast`. Never define duplicate types locally.
- Components: functional, ≤150 lines; extract hooks for logic. One component per file.
- No inline styles for document content — the editor is style-less by design (Invariant #1).
- Transformers (`packages/transformers`) must be pure functions with snapshot tests; no I/O inside.
- API routes: Fastify with typed schemas; workers never share memory with API.
- Naming: kebab-case files, PascalCase components, camelCase functions.

## Hard Invariants (from architecture.md §5 — violating these is a bug)
1. No font-size/color/spacing controls or nodes in the editor schema.
2. Citations stored as `citeKey` only; rendering happens at compile time.
3. `packages/ast` is the single type source of truth.
4. Compilation is sandboxed and async, always.

## Testing
- New transformer logic → snapshot test required in same PR.
- Zod schema change → update tests + both consumers (web, api) in same change.

## When Uncertain
- If a requirement is ambiguous, ask ONE concise question instead of guessing.
- If a library API might have changed post-training, say so and check docs rather than hallucinating.
